## AI IDE Instructions

When using Cursor, Copilot, Windsurf, or any AI IDE:

### DO:
- Tell the AI which stage you're in
- Share relevant existing files as context
- Give exact "Done when" criteria from the task list
- Verify the fix works before moving on

### DON'T:
- Let the AI add services from future stages
- Accept Celery imports (use ARQ in Stages 1-3)
- Accept Neo4j setup (use PostgreSQL JSONB in Stages 1-3)
- Accept Temporal/NATS/OPA/Keycloak (Stage 4 only)
- Let the AI "refactor while fixing" — minimum change principle

### Prompt Template:
```
I am working on Co-Op, Stage [X], Task [T-XXX]: [task name].

Current services: [list from stage guide]
Stage constraints: No [list forbidden tech for this stage]

Files to review:
- [file1]
- [file2]

Done when: [exact criteria from task list]

Please implement this task.
```

